        <para id="id13153413">When the above-mentioned supply and demand curves are drawn on the same axis, we see that the two curves meet at a specific point, namely when the price is R0,60, the sellers are prepared to supply 300 heads of cabbage and the buyers are prepared to purchase 300 heads of cabbage at that price. This price is known as the MARKET EQUILIBRIUM PRICE </para>
        <para id="id14369530">and it represents the price at which the buyer and the seller are prepared to barter. At any other price the parties will not be able to agree and they will not be prepared to conclude a transaction. </para>
      </section>
